The Positive Left License is a license which allows for the modification of materials on any piece of media with this license applied. The license also requires the following requirements be met in order to properly comply with terms disclosed on the license:

1. COPYLEFT - All works derived from works using this license must also use this license and must also allow for users to stem off of from them. No exclusions will be made for this.

2. NO DEFAMATION/DISCRIMINATION - Works using this license must not use the original work in a manner which could be considered defamatory/discriminatory. Examples of discriminatory content are:
- Active calls for the extermination/genocide of minority groups (i.e. Palestinians)
- Content which advocates for far-right ideologies (such as fascism, Nazism, white supremacy, etc.)
- Content which actively uses slurs in a discriminatory manner
This also includes original works created using this license.

3. LIABILITY - The original owner of the work disclaims all liabilities that arise from misuse or violations of this license. Failure to use this license with terms above will lead to your license being revoked, and legal action is allowed to be taken by the original owner of the work if needed. 
